<taxonomicName box="[282,625,1746,1772]" pageId="28" pageNumber="709">ORNITHISCHIA Seeley, 1888</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="709" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="28.[130,776,1810,2028]" box="[132,270,1810,1836]" pageId="28" pageNumber="709">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[130,776,1810,2028]" pageId="28" pageNumber="709">With the exception of thyreophorans, the ornithischian dinosaurs of Angeac-Charente are mainly represented by isolated teeth. Most of these teeth show evidence of pre-burial transport and are either broken or eroded. However, the few remaining well-preserved teeth indicate a great diversity of ornithischians, represented by at least five families.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
